Table~\ref{tab:leaderboard} presents the primary ranking. CAMEL-AI, SmolagentS, and FlowSearcher form an indistinguishable top tier (pairwise Elo gaps of 6--77 are non-significant at $p > 0.2$), a tier that is decisively separated from the bottom six by a 341~Elo gap ($p < 0.001$ by permutation test).

\paragraph{What separates the tiers?} Table~\ref{tab:profiles} decomposes the composite into its constituent dimensions. The top-3 agents achieve high URL reachability (CAMEL-AI 0.91, FlowSearcher 0.80, SmolagentS 0.71), meaning they actually navigate the sandbox and cite real pages. The bottom six split into two failure modes: \emph{wholesale fabrication} (GPT-Researcher 0.03, Langchain-ODR 0.004, II-Researcher 0.002, STORM 0.0 reachability), and \emph{output collapse} (DeerFlow, LDR, STORM cite very few URLs at all). The fabricators generate plausible-looking sandbox URLs that do not correspond to any page that actually exists.

This failure is decoupled from report quality. GPT-Researcher achieves the highest scores on url\_coverage (0.191), checklist judge (0.610), analysis depth (0.301), and presentation (0.682), outperforming the top tier on most quality dimensions. Yet its composite score is 0.030, because the truthfulness gate reduces its effective score to 10\% of its quality.

